Name: ps
Description: The command displays information about processes on the system.

Arguments.Name: A
Arguments.Description: Display information about other users' processes, including those without controlling terminals.

Arguments.Name: a
Arguments.Description: Display information about other users' processes as well as your own.

Arguments.Name: C
Arguments.Description: The `-C` option changes the way the CPU percentage is calculated by using a specific method.

Arguments.Name: c
Arguments.Description: Changes the output of the "command" column to display only the executable name.

Arguments.Name: E
Arguments.Description: Display the environment along with process information.

Arguments.Name: e
Arguments.Description: Displaying the environment without reflecting changes post-process launch.

Arguments.Name: f
Arguments.Description: Displays detailed information about processes including user, process ID, parent process ID, CPU usage, process start time, controlling terminal, elapsed CPU usage, and associated command.

Arguments.Name: G
Arguments.Description: Display information about processes running with specified real group IDs.

Arguments.Name: g
Arguments.Description: Display information about processes with the specified process group leaders.

Arguments.Name: h
Arguments.Description: Repeat the information header as needed to ensure one header per page of information.

Arguments.Name: j
Arguments.Description: Prints information associated with specific process attributes.

Arguments.Name: L
Arguments.Description: List the set of keywords available for the `-O` and `-o` options.

Arguments.Name: l
Arguments.Description: Display information associated with specific process details and attributes.

Arguments.Name: M
Arguments.Description: The `-M` option displays the threads corresponding to each task.

Arguments.Name: m
Arguments.Description: The `-m` argument sorts processes based on memory usage instead of other criteria.
